article.headline: Stetson 65, S.C.-Upstate 60
article.story: DELAND, Fla. -- A.J. Smith scored 19 points and dished out five assists to lead Stetson to a 65-60 win over South Carolina-Upstate on Saturday night in both teams' regular-season finale. Brandon Williams finished with 14 points and Mark Lohuis added 10 for the Hatters (7-22, 5-15 Atlantic Sun Conference), who failed to qualify for the conference tournament. Joel Naburgs had 12 points for Stetson. The Spartans (6-23, 6-14) will also miss the tournament -- which starts March 4 -- because of NCAA reclassifying rules. Stetson opened with a 10-1 run and led 37-30 at halftime. USC-Upstate tied the game at 49 with 8:43 to play before the Hatters regained command with a 10-0 run. Ryan LeGates had 18 points and Nick Schneiders had 14 points for USC-Upstate. Stetson knocked down 12 3-pointers compared to the Spartans, who finished with eight.
